                                                    boolean forAll,
                                                    JDDNode statesOfInterest)
                                             throws PrismException
        Model check a multi-objective query (from the contents of a strategy operator). Return the result as a StateValues object (usually this gives values for all states, but for a multi-objective query, we just give a single value, i.e., the statesOfInterest should be a singleton set).

        Parameters:
        exprs - The list of Expressions specifying the objectives
        forAll - Are we checking "for all strategies" (true) or "there exists a strategy" (false)? [irrelevant for numerical (=?) queries]
        statesOfInterest - the states of interest
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • computeRestrictedNext

        protected StateValues computeRestrictedNext(JDDNode tr,
                                            JDDNode a,
                                            StateValues x,
                                            boolean min)
        Given a value vector x, compute the probability: v(s) = min/max sched [ Sum_s' P_sched(s,s')*x(s') ] for s labeled with a, v(s) = 0 for s not labeled with a. Clears the StateValues object x.
        Parameters:
        tr - the transition matrix
        a - the set of states labeled with a
        x - the value vector
        min - compute min instead of max

      • checkWeakAbsorbing

        private boolean checkWeakAbsorbing(JDDNode dd,
                                   NondetModel model)
        Check whether state set represented by dd is "weak absorbing", i.e. whether set is closed under all successors. Note: does not deref dd.
